    "In this way, we can identify the explainers' computational limits.",
    "From the perspective of memory, we consider only algorithms that do not exceed the 64GB of RAM requirement, which is the RAM size on which we are conducting experiments, while from the perspective of computational times, an algorithm will be considered intractable if it takes longer than one day for global explainers and more than 3 h for a single explanation of local ones.",
